Mirrors and reflective surfaces do not show any trace of the Lasombra.  Some say this oddity occurs because the Lasombra have no souls; others claim that it is part of their Obtenebration Disciplne.  Whatever the cause, Lasombra (and their clothes and carried possessions)do not show up in any sort of reflective surface, such as mirrors. pools of water, reflective windows, photographs and black and white film (which uses a reflective silver emulsifier). pg. 43 LotN Revised<br>
<br>
Cast No Reflection (1 Trait Flaw):<br>
Like the Lasombra, you cast no reflection in mirrors or mirrored surfaces.  Obviously, this Flaw constitutes as a Breach of the Masquerade, and it can draw a great deal of attention in certain circumstances.  Lasombra cannot take this flaw for free traits.  pg.121 LotN Revised<br>
<br>
<br>
My opinion.  Unless a character who is Lasombra or is cursed with such a flaw has their image captured by anything other than a digital camera, they do not show up in the image.  But once again, this is a Staff call.<br>
<br>
Hope this has helped.<br>
<br>
